moves.1. e4 e5 2. Bc4 Nf6 3. d3 c6 4. Nf3 Qc7: Vienna game - a little early to open the center, but ok I guess.
moves.6. exd5 cxd5 7. Bb3: Not Bb5+ as this will only force him to develop a pice.
moves.7... Be7: Not sure this is good, I was expecting Bg4 to keep the pressure.
moves.8. Re1 Nc6 9. Nxe5: White win a pawn due to the problems black have after Bf4.
moves.9... Nxe5 10. Bf4 Nfd7: I would have played Bd6 to remove the pressure from the Queen, but then he has the problem with the king - I believe that 5.-,d5 was a little too fast.
moves.11. d4 f6 12. Nc3: Always keep the pressure if possible, there is no reason to take the night yet if you can get more.
moves.12... Bb4: Mistake, black had to move the Queen out of the line, Bd6 would still loose, but not so fast.
moves.13. dxe5 Bxc3: Loosing the queen, but 13.-,fxe5 was not much better due to 14.Nxd5.
moves.14. exf6+ Bxe1 15. Bxc7 Bb4: I guess black just wanna finish - this is a mate in 3, but why even consider to defend himself.
moves.16. Qxd5: Black resigned, there is a mate on f7, max 3 moves left, i.e. 16.-,Rf8 17.Qe6+,Be7 18.Qxe7#
